      <div class="legal-content">
        <p class="lead">ApolloNews respects the intellectual property rights of others and expects users and content sources to do the same. We comply with the Digital Millennium Copyright Act (DMCA) and respond promptly to notices of alleged copyright infringement.</p>

        <h4 class="fw-bold mt-4">How ApolloNews Works</h4>
        <p>ApolloNews is a news aggregation platform. We display brief summaries (headlines, descriptions, and thumbnail images) automatically retrieved via licensed third-party news APIs. Every item links to the original article on its source website. We do not republish full articles or claim copyright ownership over third-party content.</p>
        <p>We believe our use of brief excerpts for informational discovery constitutes fair use under applicable copyright law. However, we take all infringement claims seriously and will investigate and remove content expeditiously.</p>

        <h4 class="fw-bold mt-4">Filing a DMCA Takedown Notice</h4>
        <p>If you are a copyright owner and believe that content on ApolloNews infringes your copyright, please submit a written notice to us containing <strong>all</strong> of the following:</p>
        <ol>
          <li>Your full legal name, address, telephone number, and email address</li>
          <li>A description of the copyrighted work you claim has been infringed</li>
          <li>The specific URL(s) on our Site where the allegedly infringing material appears</li>
          <li>A statement that you have a good faith belief that use of the material is not authorised by the copyright owner, its agent, or the law</li>
          <li>A statement, made under penalty of perjury, that the information in your notice is accurate and that you are the copyright owner or authorised to act on the copyright owner's behalf</li>
          <li>Your electronic or physical signature</li>
        </ol>
        <p>Please submit your notice via our <a href="/contact">Contact page</a> with the subject line "<strong>DMCA Takedown Notice</strong>".</p>

        <h4 class="fw-bold mt-4">Our Response Process</h4>
        <p>Upon receipt of a valid DMCA notice, we will:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Acknowledge receipt within 48 hours</li>
          <li>Investigate the claim within 5 working days</li>
          <li>Remove or disable access to the allegedly infringing content if the claim is valid</li>
          <li>Notify the party who provided the content of the takedown</li>
        </ul>

        <h4 class="fw-bold mt-4">Counter-Notification</h4>
        <p>If content you provided was removed due to a DMCA notice and you believe the removal was incorrect, you may submit a counter-notification via our Contact page. Counter-notifications must include the same identifying information as a takedown notice along with a statement, under penalty of perjury, that the removed material was removed by mistake or misidentification.</p>

        <h4 class="fw-bold mt-4">Repeat Infringers</h4>
        <p>ApolloNews has a policy of terminating or blocking access for users or sources that are found to be repeat infringers of intellectual property rights.</p>

        <h4 class="fw-bold mt-4">Abuse of DMCA Process</h4>
        <p>Submitting a false DMCA notice may constitute perjury under applicable law. ApolloNews reserves the right to seek damages from any party that abuses the DMCA notification process.</p>
